column6: SURRY HILLS - Bed in a shared room B2
column7: Surry Hills is an urban centre with great restaurants and an energetic nightlife. Our house is located right behind the popular Oxford Street and just 10 minutes walk from Museum Station and 15 minutes from Central Station. You can also count on nearby bus stops  running every 3-5 minutes directly to either the world-famous Sydney Opera House or Bondi Beach, one of the most beautiful and popular beach to visit in Australia. I'm sure you'll like it!

column11: Surry Hills is an evolving area known for its stylish cultural and cafe scene. Terraced houses on Crown and Cleveland streets showcase hip coffee joints, fashion boutiques and global eateries. Trendy pubs, wine bars and galleries dot the area around Surry Hills Library, a community hub with a contemporary, sustainable design. Held once a month, Surry Hills Markets lure shoppers for snacks and vintage goods.
column13: Transport NSW has a tap & go system that allows you to load a balance on an Opal Card to use on all types of public transport across the state. We recommend using an Opal Card during your travels as it much more convenient and efficient as you don't have to stop and buy a new ticket each time you travel. Opal Cards are free, just load a balance as you go.

There may be 1 or 2 surfboards in the apartment (depends where I'm travelling to) which you would be welcome to use.

column6: Stunning modern studio apartment in Sydney CBD
column7: A light, bright, ultra modern apartment in the heart of the city.  The apartment itself is clean, comfortable and is a joy to live in. The apartment is owned by a young professional couple, and the only reason it is let out is because we are overseas. The shared facilities are simply stunning rivalling any 5* hotel. There is a 50m swimming pool which is both outside and inside. A jacuzzi, steam room and sauna all accompany the pool, alongside a sun deck. A cardio and weight gym are also on site.
column8: The award winning 'Lumiere' building offers cutting edge living in the city centre. Guests can expect a comfortable, clean and tidy apartment with views south over the World Tower and Geroge Street.  Described as a 'studio' the apartment is well split up with the kitchen and bed in separate spaces. The apartment makes good use of the space, and comes equipped with cooking facilities, TV, iron, washing machine/dryer and air-con.
